 Goods worth several millions of naira were, last Saturday, destroyed as fire gutted the Obi Isiedo Foodstuff Market in Nnewi, Anambra State. The disclosure was made in a statement issued to journalists in Awka, on Sunday, by Martin Agbili, Chief Fire Officer in Anambra State. Agbili said that the fire service received a distress call at 10:25pm on Saturday about a fire outbreak at Okpuno Egbu Market, Umudim Nnewi. He said that fire trucks and firefighters at Nnewi were deployed to the scene of the incident to contain the inferno with additional emergency response mobilised from the headquarters in Awka The fire chief said that the cause of the fire outbreak was still unknown, but would be confirmed after investigation. Agbili said that no casualty was recorded in the incident, stating however that parts of the market were affected. He added that the firemen responded swiftly to curtail the fire which lasted four hours. Agbili, who commiserated with the victims, commended the members of the public and security agencies for the timely information and assistance in putting out the fire. “Also, I want to appreciate all my firefighters who toiled day and night in ensuring the safety of lives and property of Anambra people,” he said. (NAN). 